	<h2>Paul's Story</h2>
	<p>We first met Paul when he entered our shelter program, carrying only what he had on him. From the beginning, it was clear Paul was seeking more than just shelter — he was looking for hope and a place to belong.&nbsp;While in the shelter program, Paul found employment and eventually secured his own apartment. He has even chosen to become a Senior Soldier --&nbsp;a full member of our church -- and he lives now to serve others. One example shows his impact: &nbsp;</p>
	<blockquote>A gentleman, who was a native Spanish speaker, came to church.Paul was the first to greet him, and when he began speaking in Spanish, the man’s face lit up.Paul invited him to sit together, and at that moment, a connection was made.Paul didn’t just share his language—he shared his story. He told the man, “If I could make it through, so can you.”Paul’s life is an example of the power of community and personal testimony.Paul embodies a hope that changes lives.</blockquote>
	<br>
	<h2>Join us in Making this Vision a Reality</h2>
	<p>The need is urgent, and the time to act is now! The cost for the new Hope House is $10&nbsp;million.&nbsp;We invite you to join us in this critical and transformative effort. To reach this goal, pledges and contributions made over a three-to-five-year period will be solicited.&nbsp;A variety of naming opportunities are available.</p>
	<h2>Donate Now</h2>
	<p>There are multiple ways you can contribute to this important initiative.&nbsp;This is your opportunity to make a difference.&nbsp;</p>
